NASA flagbearer Raila Odinga unveils his manifesto next week that promises equal opportunities, democracy and devolution after 11 political parties endorsed his presidential bid.Former Lands CS Charity Ngilu, Wiper governor nominee Wavinya Ndeti, and Makueni Governor Kivutha Kibwana will lead the pack which will bring together Narc, Federal Party of Kenya, Maendeleo Party, Muungano Party and Chama Cha Uzalendo.The parties will convene the National Delegates Councils across the city at various venues. &ldquo;I will not release the details right now,&rdquo; said head of Cord Secretariat Norman Magaya. The functions meant to endorse the flagbearer were postponed last Friday after parties failed to secure the venues for the National Delegates Conference.